{
  "slug": "get-crawler-parameters",
  "title": "Get Crawler Parameters",
  "description": "Retrieve the list of configurable input parameters for a specific crawler",
  "category": "Crawler",
  "metadata": {
    "method": "GET",
    "endpoint": "/v1/crawlers/{crawler_hash}/params",
    "requiresAuth": true
  },
  "content": {
    "introduction": "This endpoint returns all configurable input parameters for a specific crawler. The response is organized into two main sections: `task` and `squid`.\n\n## Response Structure\n\nThe response contains:\n- **task**: Object containing task-level parameters (parameter name as key)\n- **squid**: Object containing squid-level parameters and functions\n- **squid.functions**: Optional add-on features with extra credit costs\n\n{{RENDER:taskLevelFields}}\n\n{{RENDER:squidLevelFields}}\n\n{{RENDER:functionsFields}}",
    "sections": {
      "taskLevelFields": {
        "title": "Task-level Parameter Fields",
        "fields": [
          {
            "path": "task.{parameter_name}.type",
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Data type (string, int, boolean, etc.)",
            "example": "\"string\""
          },
          {
            "path": "task.{parameter_name}.group",
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Logical grouping (e.g., \"url\", \"location\")",
            "example": "\"url\""
          },
          {
            "path": "task.{parameter_name}.regex",
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Validation pattern for string inputs",
            "example": "\"^https?://.*\""
          },
          {
            "path": "task.{parameter_name}.required",
            "type": "boolean",
            "description": "Whether the parameter is mandatory",
            "example": "true"
          },
          {
            "path": "task.{parameter_name}.default",
            "type": "string | number | boolean | null",
            "description": "Default value if not provided",
            "example": "null"
          },
          {
            "path": "task.{parameter_name}.attribute",
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Internal attribute name",
            "example": "\"url\""
          },
          {
            "path": "task.{parameter_name}.is_params",
            "type": "boolean",
            "description": "Whether it's used for URL parameter generation",
            "example": "true"
          }
        ]
      },
      "squidLevelFields": {
        "title": "Squid-level Parameter Fields",
        "fields": [
          {
            "path": "squid.{parameter_name}.type",
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Data type of the parameter",
            "example": "\"string\""
          },
          {
            "path": "squid.{parameter_name}.allowed",
            "type": "array",
            "description": "Array of valid values (for enum types)",
            "example": "[\"en\", \"es\", \"fr\"]"
          },
          {
            "path": "squid.{parameter_name}.default",
            "type": "string | number | boolean | null",
            "description": "Default value if not provided",
            "example": "\"en\""
          },
          {
            "path": "squid.{parameter_name}.required",
            "type": "boolean",
            "description": "Whether the parameter is mandatory",
            "example": "false"
          },
          {
            "path": "squid.{parameter_name}.attribute",
            "type": "string",
            "description": "Internal attribute name",
            "example": "\"language\""
          }
        ]
      },
      "functionsFields": {
        "title": "Functions (Optional Add-ons) Fields",
        "fields": [
          {
            "path": "squid.functions.{function_name}.sort",
            "type": "integer",
            "description": "Display order of the function",
            "example": "1"
          },
          {
            "path": "squid.functions.{function_name}.default",
            "type": "boolean",
            "description": "Whether the function is enabled by default",
            "example": "false"
          },
          {
            "path": "squid.functions.{function_name}.credits_per_function",
            "type": "number",
            "description": "Extra credits charged per row when this function is enabled",
            "example": "0.5"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    "parameters": [
      {
        "name": "crawler_hash",
        "type": "string",
        "required": true,
        "description": "The unique identifier (hash/id) of the crawler",
        "example": "4734d096159ef05210e0e1677e8be823"
      }
    ],
    "headers": [
      {
        "key": "Authorization",
        "value": "Token YOUR_API_KEY",
        "required": true,
        "description": "Your API authentication token"
      },
      {
        "key": "Content-Type",
        "value": "application/json",
        "required": false,
        "description": "Content type of the request"
      }
    ],
    "proTips": [
      {
        "type": "tip",
        "content": "The response structure uses parameter names as object keys. Access task parameters via params.task.url, squid parameters via params.squid.language, etc."
      },
      {
        "type": "note",
        "content": "Functions under squid.functions are optional add-ons. Each function has a credits_per_function cost applied per result row when enabled."
      },
      {
        "type": "warning",
        "content": "Pay attention to 'allowed' arrays in squid parameters - these only accept specific values. Sending invalid values will cause validation errors."
      },
      {
        "type": "tip",
        "content": "Use 'regex' patterns in task parameters to validate input before sending. This helps catch errors early and reduces failed tasks."
      },
      {
        "type": "tip",
        "content": "Parameters with 'group' field are logically related. For location-based crawlers, you'll typically need to provide all parameters in the 'location' group."
      }
    ]
  },
  "seo": {
    "title": "Get Crawler Parameters - lobstr.io API Documentation",
    "description": "Learn how to retrieve input parameters for a specific crawler using the lobstr.io API. Understand task-level and squid-level parameters."
  }
}